I added some pragmas in ed04463 (part of the old pull request branch) to prevent some compilation warnings related to bullet headers, but there is a [stubborn warning that it not obeying the pragmas](http://build.osrfoundation.org/job/gazebo-any-devel-trusty-amd64-no-gpu/548/warnings17Result/):

~~~
In file included from /usr/include/bullet_2.82/bullet/LinearMath/btQuickprof.h:22:0,
                 from /usr/include/bullet_2.82/bullet/LinearMath/btMatrixX.h:20,
                 from /var/lib/jenkins/workspace/gazebo-any-devel-trusty-amd64-no-gpu/gazebo/deps/opende/src/step_bullet_pgs_wrapper.cpp:37:
/usr/include/bullet_2.82/bullet/LinearMath/btScalar.h:337:13: warning: 'btInfinityMask' defined but not used [-Wunused-variable]
  static  int btInfinityMask = 0x7F800000;
             ^
~~~

Note that [step_bullet_pgs_wrapper.cpp:37](https://bitbucket.org/rosebudflyaway/gazebo/src/1aa11f1bdf0b2607d7abf1c61517676854b7f3d4/deps/opende/src/step_bullet_pgs_wrapper.cpp#step_bullet_pgs_wrapper.cpp-37) is inside the pragma push/pop block. Is this a gcc bug?
